2
Responsibilities: 

Coordinate situations end to end from all over the world and provide explanations that require expertise and in-depth knowledge of warranty processes and policies.
Manage day-to-day daily operations of the warranty claims processing team 
Demonstrate accountability for managing key KPIs and SLAs.
Resolve team`s complex queries on claims validation of warranty claims based on technical knowledge of the commercial automotive & its sub-components.
Perform process/control plan audits for warranty corrective actions and best practices to ensure status is captured and reported with well-defined corrective action plans taken to closure.
Ensure all warranty mitigation and improvement corrective actions are properly documented and verified (evidence of revised documents or on-site reviews)
Coordinate the creation of monthly reports/data collection to improve warranty performance while driving continuous improvement programs (quality incentive programs, quality improvement meetings, etc.)
Perform process/control plan audits for warranty corrective actions and best practices to ensure status is capture and reported with well-defined corrective action plans taken to closure.
Support internal audits and follow up on corrective actions
Ensure common and accepted safety protocols for the quality group are implemented as needed and compliance is maintained
Support and perform other duties/projects as assigned
